---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy · memoato" description="Privacy policy." canonicalPath="/privacy">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <h1 class="page-title">Privacy policy</h1>
      <p>
        memoato stores only what’s needed to run the app: your account and the data you log. We don’t sell your data.
      </p>
      <h2>Data we store</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Account details: email and username.</li>
        <li>Your trackers (categories): name, emoji, color, goals.</li>
        <li>Your logged entries: numbers and timestamps (and optional per-entry notes).</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Data you control</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>You can edit and delete entries.</li>
        <li>You can export your data from the profile page.</li>
        <li>You can delete your account, which removes your account and logged data.</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Analytics</h2>
      <p>
        We use Databuddy for privacy-friendly analytics on memoato.com and app.memoato.com to understand product usage
        (not to identify you). Analytics requests may be blocked by common privacy tools.
      </p>
      <h2>Emails</h2>
      <p>
        We send transactional emails for account verification and password resets. We do not send marketing emails.
      </p>
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Questions or requests: <a href="mailto:hello@memoato.com">hello@memoato.com</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
